				"category": "offensive",
				"description": {
					"value": "<p>While it has persistent bleed damage from the fisher's fishing line Strike, a creature has a fishhook embedded in it. The creature can't move farther away from the fisher (though it can move laterally). The fisher can reel the creature in as a single action with the attack and manipulate trait, attempting an @Check[athletics|against:fortitude] check against the creature's Fortitude DC. On a success, the creature takes @Damage[2d4[slashing]] damage and is pulled 10 feet closer to the fisher (double the damage and distance on a critical success).</p>",
